---
description: Component authoring conventions for packages/core
globs:
  - packages/core/**/*.tsx
---

Every component in `packages/core` must:

1. Use `React.forwardRef` and set `ComponentName.displayName`.
2. Accept and forward a `className` prop ‚Äî always merge with `cn()` from `@id-components/utils`.
3. Define all style variants with `cva()` ‚Äî no inline ternaries for class logic.
4. Export its Props type.
5. Be built on a Radix UI primitive where accessibility is critical.

Never import `gsap` directly. Motion goes through `useMotion()` and `useTimeline()` from
`@id-components/motion`.

TypeScript strict: no `any`, no `!` non-null assertions without a comment explaining why.
